result.title: Похожие куски кода с разным временем выполнения
result.content:
So i've been trying to solve Е recently (the problem), and i kept getting TL10 for a long time.

As a result i now have 2 submissions (24325463 and 24325486), one of which works almost twice as fast as the other one, while essentially they differ in the indexation order of the lookup table.

What makes it even more interesting is that these 2 submissions (which are basically the same as the previous two): 24325728 and 24325694, run with a difference of 450ms with the texts differing only in the amount of the empty strings.

Can smb explain this please?
